First off, the place is actually called, "New Golden China", and don't waste your time here! They never actually have anyone that speaks clear or decent English taking orders. Though I suppose if you're looking for that extreme authenticity in Chinese food. . . Anyway, on top of that,  out of the three times we've ordered from there, the food is only ok and tends to be on the greasy side.  Then, this last time we ordered, we were promised that the food would arrive in 45 minutes to an hour. It arrived almost 90 minutes after it was ordered, and was completely someone else's order!  Our choices at that point, promised from the Mgr was too get it completely remade, which would take another 45 minutes to an hour! So was able to convey with the partially literate employee that I did not want that and had to argue to get a full refund, which I did finally get.

